      • generalizePositive

        public java.util.Collection<edu.cs.ai.log4KR.relational.probabilisticConditionalLogic.syntax.RelationalConditional> generalizePositive(edu.cs.ai.log4KR.relational.probabilisticConditionalLogic.syntax.RelationalConditional c,
                                                                                                                                       java.util.Collection<java.util.Collection<edu.cs.ai.log4KR.relational.probabilisticConditionalLogic.syntax.RelationalConditional>> classifiedClasses)
        Generalizes positive canonically. Which means an disjunction of equality constraints which are generates with each variable and its corresponding constant. The reflexive knowledge has an exclusive treatment. for example: c = flies(X) (flies(X))[0.6636035435403175]<((X=Sylvester + X=Kirby) + X=Bully)>);(flies(Tweety))[3.9682291970525344E-9])
        Parameters:
        c - qualified conditional of the query
        classifiedClasses - the classified classes of the ground instance (those with equal probability)
        Returns:
        generalization
